Package: clipboard-extension
Architecture: all
Maintainer: haibachvan <haibachvan@local>
Depends: gnome-shell (>= 49), libglib2.0-bin
Recommends: libgdk-pixbuf-2.0-0
Description: Smart clipboard manager GNOME Shell extension
 A lightweight GNOME Shell extension that keeps the last 25 clipboard items
 (text + images), supports pinning items across reboots, and recalls them
 from a Super+V overlay picker that auto-pastes into the focused app.
 .
 Event-driven (no polling), privacy-aware (skips password-manager content),
 and ships system-wide under /usr/share/gnome-shell/extensions/.
